{
  "text": "providing a valuable tool for diagnosis. The fusion partners of EWSR1 belong to several gene families, mainly encoding transcription factors. These proteins join the amino terminal of the EWSR1 gene with the carboxy terminal of an ETS gene family member. This fusion not only abrogates the RNA splicing function of EWSR1 but also removes essential transactivating control regions of the ETS gene partner. As many as 90% of the translocations involve the EWSR1 gene in the form of t(11;22)(q24;q12) translocation, which juxtaposes EWSR1 at 22q12 with the FLI1 gene on chromosome 11q24 [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "41557735"
